column1: Who will win the 2020 Missouri Democratic primary?
column5: ['Joe Biden', 'Michael Bloomberg', 'Pete Buttigieg', 'Amy Klobuchar', 'Bernie Sanders', 'Elizabeth Warren', 'Someone else']

column6: Biden (the Democratic machine at least) should continue his dominance from Super Tuesday
Latest poll shows Sanders is down by only 4%, so there is a chance of an upset.
Biden has the edge thanks to support from older and black voters. Might be tight though.

Most recent poll has former Vice President Biden Biden up by 4. https://www.kxan.com/news/your-local-election-hq/exclusive-poll-shows-joe-biden-ahead-of-bernie-sanders-in-missouri-presidential-primary/ FiveThirtyEight has him as a heavy favorite. Going to go slightly higher than consensus in favor of Biden.
Updating to incorporate Super Tuesday results

Although we haven't had too many forecasts in this state I think its safe to say that the voters very much favour Biden. Before Iowa he had a poll lead of around 20 which makes him a comfortable favourite. Although the last poll only gave him a lead of 5 points I think we can assume his polling will have improved significantly since then.
Raised Joe Biden's chances after Super Tuesday

Biden's strong performance in South Carolina highlights his broad support in the south, which only be further proved on Super Tuesday. While there aren't any polls to base a predication on, South Carolina and the results of the other Southern Super Tuesday State confirm and will more than likely reconfirm that Biden will most definitely sweep the south.
Adjusting in light of Buttigieg dropping out.
Updating with new prior after 538 has incorporated this weekend's results.
